---
import Layout from '@/components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Crew Culture - Building Strong Ruck Crew Identity" 
  description="Learn how to build strong crew culture, create traditions, and foster unbreakable bonds within your ruck club."
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <header class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Crew Culture</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-muted max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Culture is what happens when the leader isn't looking. Build a culture so strong it carries itself.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Core Principles -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-foreground">The 9 Pillars of Crew Culture</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Pillar 1 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-foreground">1. Shared Purpose</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Align around common goals and motivations for rucking. Everyone should know <em>why</em> they're there, not just <em>what</em> they're doing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 2 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-foreground">2. Mutual Respect</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Value each member's contributions and differences. Respect isn't earned — it's given to everyone until they prove otherwise.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 3 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-foreground">3. Shared Suffering</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Embrace challenges together. The miles you grind together create bonds that no other activity can match. Lean into the hard rucks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 4 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-foreground">4. Celebration</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Recognize achievements, both big and small, as a group. Celebrate PRs, consistency milestones, birthdays, and just showing up.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 5 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-foreground">5. Tradition</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Create rituals and routines that become part of the club's identity. Traditions create continuity and belonging.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 6 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-foreground">6. Storytelling</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Share experiences and lessons learned to inspire others. Every ruck is a story. Help members tell theirs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 7 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-foreground">7. Inclusivity</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Ensure everyone feels they belong and can contribute. A strong culture includes rather than excludes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 8 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-foreground">8. Accountability</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Hold each other to shared standards and commitments. In a crew, everyone watches out for everyone.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pillar 9 -->
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted-50 p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-foreground">9. Fun</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Maintain enjoyment and camaraderie as central to the experience. If it's not fun, why do it? The laughs matter as much as the miles.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Building Traditions -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Building Traditions</h2>
      <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
        <p>Traditions give your crew identity. Here are ideas:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside mt-4">
          <li><strong>Opening circle:</strong> Start each ruck with a brief check-in</li>
          <li><strong>Closing debrief:</strong> End every ruck with lessons learned</li>
          <li><strong>Nicknames:</strong> Earned through effort, not given freely</li>
          <li><strong>Anniversary rucks:</strong> Celebrate the club's founding annually</li>
          <li><strong>Themed rucks:</strong> Costume rucks, birthday rucks, milestones</li>
          <li><strong>Post-ruck ritual:</strong> Coffee, breakfast, or food somewhere specific</li>
          <li><strong>Club motto:</strong> Something short and memorable that captures your spirit</li>
          <li><strong>Challenge events:</strong> Annual rucks that become legendary</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Culture Killers -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Culture Killers to Avoid</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-red-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-red-700">Elitism</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-600">Making new members feel unwelcome or inferior drives them away.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-red-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-red-700">Gossip</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-600">Talking behind members' backs destroys trust quickly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-red-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-red-700">No Show Policy</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-600">Missing without notice should be addressed, not ignored.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-red-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-red-700">Burning Out</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-600">Overtraining members or forcing intensity leads to dropout.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Measuring Culture Health -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Measuring Culture Health</h2>
      <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
        <p>Ask your crew regularly:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside mt-4">
          <li>Do I feel welcome here?</li>
          <li>Do I look forward to rucks?</li>
          <li>Do I trust my crew members?</li>
          <li>Am I growing as a rucker?</li>
          <li>Would I recommend this crew to a friend?</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Resources -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-muted-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-muted-200">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Downloadable Resources</h2>
        <p class="text-muted mb-4">Tools for building crew culture:</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/checklists/crew-culture.pdf" class="btn btn-primary" download>
            Download Crew Culture Checklist (PDF)
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <nav class="flex gap-4">
      <a href="/lead/ruck-clubs" class="btn btn-secondary">
        ← Back to Ruck Clubs
      </a>
      <a href="/lead" class="btn btn-utility">
        All Leadership Resources
      </a>
    </nav>
  </div>
</Layout>
